---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="resume -- alexander campos" description="Operations and software. Six years regulated finance. Three shipped products. Legal recoveries, compliance, monitoring, resolution.">
  <article class="resume">
    <h1>Resume</h1>

    <section class="summary">
      <p>
        Operations and software. Six years in regulated finance - BSA, AML, KYC, SCRA, GLBA, NCUA, CFPB, UDAAP, fraud controls. Process design, monitoring systems, reporting pipelines, enterprise integration. Also builds independently: three production products shipped solo, one with paying users. The pattern across everything - own the operation end-to-end, build the tools it needs, hand it off running.
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Skills</h2>

      <h3>Operations & Systems</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Process Modernization · Failure-Surface Mapping · Dependency Sequencing ·
        KPI/OKR Frameworks · Executive Reporting · Regulatory Compliance (NCUA, CFPB)
      </p>

      <h3>Data</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        SQL (Postgres, Snowflake) · Python · Splunk · Pipeline Monitoring ·
        Looker · QuickSight · Power Platform (BI, Apps, Automate)
      </p>

      <h3>Development</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        TypeScript · Python · React · Node.js · Electron · Next.js · Astro · SQLite/FTS5 · Vite · Zustand ·
        nilearn · scikit-learn · scipy · matplotlib
      </p>

      <h3>AI Infrastructure</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Multi-Provider LLM Routing (Anthropic/OpenAI/Ollama) · Model Context Protocol ·
        Structured Tool-Use · Semantic Memory · Streaming SSE · Local-First Architecture
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Salesforce · JIRA · Confluence · SLA Governance · Vendor Risk Management · Change Control
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Experience</h2>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Capital One -- Senior Process Manager, Card Legal Recoveries Operations</h3>
          <span class="dates">June 2025 -- Present | Richmond, VA</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Built a monitoring system for a $600M+ file exchange network</strong> --
            300+ daily regulatory transmissions. Rapid prototype evolved into automated
            anomaly detection. Reduced manual monitoring by 78%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Resolved a 20,000+ account logic failure.</strong> Built an investigative
            SQL framework, isolated root cause, remediated accounts, documented the
            failure taxonomy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Zero transmission errors during $35B Discover merger integration.</strong>
            Authored full revision of the Systems Integration Guide. Worked with
            Engineering to resolve all logic ahead of cutover date.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Authored a 5-month modernization roadmap</strong> -- dependency sequencing,
            stakeholder gates, rollback protocols. Full visibility for leadership before
            resource commitment.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Picked up infrastructure tooling</strong> (Splunk, Postgres, JSON parsing).
            Built a real-time validation layer for monitoring.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Automated business reviews</strong> across 3 teams and 6 operational vectors.
            Standardized one-pagers used across the department for quarterly reviews.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Used Gemini as a structured reporting tool.</strong> Scoped instruction
            sets with validated formulas. Operational use, not conversational.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Independent Engineering</h3>
          <span class="dates">2022 -- Present</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong><a href="https://reframed.works">Reframed</a></strong> -- resume analysis platform. Live with paying users. Shipped solo in 22 days. 34 API routes, multi-provider LLM routing, Stripe billing, Neon Postgres.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong><a href="https://github.com/notaprompt/forgeframe">ForgeFrame</a></strong> -- open-source persistent memory for agents. MCP server with 12 tools, strength-based decay, constitutional persistence. 40-60% inference cost reduction.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Guardian</strong> -- local-first cognitive workspace. Desktop application with air-gapped local inference via Ollama. 60+ IPC channels, 20 backend modules. Designed for regulated environments where data residency is required.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Client work</strong> -- bilingual proposal generator for a landscaping company. Built, deployed, in use.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Apple Federal Credit Union -- Branch Operations Administrator</h3>
          <span class="dates">January 2020 -- May 2025 | Fairfax, VA</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Five years</strong>, teller to branch manager (team of 7) to enterprise
            support across 25 branches during a major merger.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built compliance tracking infrastructure</strong> -- Power BI dashboards,
            regulatory documentation (NCUA, CFPB). Reduced complaint response cycles by 50%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed a branch-wide modernization roadmap.</strong> Approved, moved
            into implementation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>B.S. Business Administration, Management and Operations</strong> -- George Mason
        University, December 2024.
      </p>
      <p class="skills">Certifications: Business Process Management · Google Data Analytics</p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <div class="resume-contact">
      <p><a href="mailto:alex@campos.works">alex@campos.works</a> · <a href="https://campos.works">campos.works</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c you are reading the resume of someone who builds systems like this one. ',
      'color: #5BF29B; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .resume {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .skills {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--white-60);
  }

  .role {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .role-header {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role-header h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .dates {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
  }

  .role ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .role li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role li strong {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
  }

  .resume-contact {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .resume-contact p {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
  }
</style>
